, j is being incremented here. So the loop continues while j hasn't reached the end of the string and s[j] is not 'W'. So the missing condition in the while loop is j ! = n && s[j] ! = 'W'. Because once you hit a 'W', the current segment ends. So the code for the while loop is:

while (j ! = n && s[j] ! = 'W') 

This loop collects all the characters in the current non-W segment. Then, for that segment, we check if both R and B are present. If any segment lacks either R or B, output is NO. So the missing code is that condition.
